Midgaard's charter records include fragment documentation of the Cairn Wars period through inherited Keeper survey lineages.
The wars' most significant consequence for Midgaard: disruption of eastern corridor supply chains accelerated Midgaard's turn toward northern forest and local agricultural supply.
The Reach Wardens' legitimacy claim — inheritance of Keeper survey rights — appears in Midgaard's derivation records as contested: the Keeper tradition had no formal succession mechanism.
Midgaard's current position on Reach Wardens: their de facto authority is acknowledged; their charter derivation is not certified.
Midgaard's Reaver Confederate administrative concern extends to the Reach: some Cairn Wars-era armed caravan leagues never formally dissolved.

